Description: Handle sliver of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp with Helios head symbol.
Production date: 199 BC (see N. Badoud, Le temps de Rhodes, 2015, 142.)
Curator's comments: Deleted pencil '305' (+?). Name Pausanias. From the same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0193.28. Trimmed.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (JB.0827)
